{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if flavour_17_trigger and flavour_17_trigger_time == time: The defection of the northern wing’s Reichstag members from the <span style="color: #007A00;">German Peasants' Party</span> to the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> has effectively ended the party as a national political force. All that remains is the original <span style="color: #38C538;">Bavarian Peasants’ League</span>, which, amid a prevailing mood of resignation, is expected to secure only a fraction of its former support in the next election, as most peasants turn further to the right in search of a solution to Germany's crisis. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if flavour_19_trigger and flavour_19_trigger_time == time: [? if bruning_time: The <span style="color: #b8996f;">**WP**</span> has issued a vote of no confidence against Brüning, formally ending any possibility of reconciliation with his government and joining the growing ranks of once-supportive bourgeois parties now in opposition. This decision comes after the party’s sole minister resigned under pressure from its anti-Brüning right wing. He is not alone in stepping down, the party’s?][? if not bruning_time: The <span style="color: #b8996f;">**WP**</span>'s?] vice chairman and effective propagandist Otto Colosser has also resigned in protest against Drewitz’s "one-man dictatorship," further accusing him of financial impropriety and other shenanigans. The internal strife has escalated to such an extent that numerous local branches have defected, effectively ending the <span style="color: #b8996f;">**WP**</span> as a viable national political force. ?]{!</p>!}

