{!<p class="other">!}[? if flavour_13_trigger and flavour_13_trigger_time == time: Brüning’s decision to sideline the Reichstag and its parties from any meaningful role in shaping his fiscal and economic policies severely undermined the legitimacy of the bourgeois parties in the eyes of their traditional electorates, due to their powerlessness to dismantle his more repugnant policies. One clear example is the plight of civil servants, who have borne the brunt of salary cuts of approximately 20 percent, pushing many toward the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>. His deflationary and austerity measures deepened the economic crisis, radicalizing the very social groups upon which these moderate parties relied for electoral support. This has led to heightened tensions between Brüning and his supporting parties, some of whom are even threatening to abandon his coalition. ?]{!</p>!}

