{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1931 and month = 6 and dnvp_ideology == "Radical": Hugenberg's attempts to cultivate a Hitler-style personality have failed, as his upper-class elitism and arrogance leave him out of touch with ordinary people suffering from the economic crisis. Frustrated by his lack of charisma, a group of industrialists has even offered a large reward for anyone who can help depose him, convinced he is steering the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> toward disaster. Adding to his troubles, the economic depression has slashed revenues from his media empire, forcing him to cut the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>'s budget by 30% just to keep the party afloat. ?]{!</p>!}

